{"type":"message","id":"463f1789","parentId":"f34b6cc5","timestamp":"2026-04-16T08:21:31.859Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_DqTb1R4zfDSSR6WJip0yIIyY|fc_0156872873475ee30169e09c0b97dc8191bbcde9d20c34868f","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"cf0e01ef350ab779e3e64b2cd3764484ac95f9fdfecfa44a9472e6d2fcc546b3\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 282,\n      \"endLine\": 326,\n      \"score\": 0.6048193012825682,\n      \"textScore\": 0.6048193012825682,\n      \"snippet\": \"- some likely Apollo and Aurelius files landed in `other` because the current bucketing is intentionally conservative\\n- for example:\\n  - `6 Prior Art Analysis Project Apol-...txt`\\n  - `7 Technical Analysis of the Janua-...txt`\\n  - `AURELIUS_CXO_v1.30...`\\n  - `MyActivity.html`\\n\\nSo the next step should be a **refinement pass**, not ingestion yet.\\n\\nMy recommendation for what I do next:\\n1. **refine classification**\\n   - re-bucket obvious Apollo/Aurelius files from `other`\\n   - treat `MyActivity.html` and `gemini_conversations_clean.md` as shared conversation sources to be project-sliced\\n\\n2. **canonicalize duplicates**\\n   - pick one preferred copy per duplicate set\\n   - mark the others as aliases\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L282-L326\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L282-L326\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c3cd34210a6282ffb4ce92b1481f3de1abf1946595b611abb950eb639319653b\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 241,\n      \"endLine\": 292,\n      \"score\": 0.5964908233758143,\n      \"textScore\": 0.5964908233758143,\n      \"snippet\": \"If you want, I can start now by generating:\\n- a corpus manifest\\n- a duplicate report\\n- initial Apollo/Aurelius project buckets\\n\\nThat’s the right next move.\\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Thu 2026-04-16 08:00 UTC] perfect, thanks. proceed\\nassistant: I’m starting with the corpus inventory and dedupe pass, then I’ll lay down the initial project buckets.\\nassistant: Done, first pass is in place.\\n\\nCreated:\\n- `vault/Clean/reports/raw_manifest.json`\\n- `vault/Clean/reports/exact_duplicates.json`\\n- `vault/Clean/reports/probable_duplicates.json`\\n- `vault/Clean/reports/raw_corpus_report.md`\\n- `vault/Clean/projects/clas\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L241-L292\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L241-L292\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c8b55d23b329dce2ab03bb1ad826ba415711770f477bec9482fbcd5f9dac0aa8\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 154,\n      \"endLine\": 204,\n      \"score\": 0.5228590252644235,\n      \"textScore\": 0.5228590252644235,\n      \"snippet\": \"What are our next steps?\\nassistant: I’m going to quickly inspect the raw corpus so the next steps are grounded in what’s actually there, not hand-wavy.\\nassistant: Yes, this is very workable. I checked the corpus, and it’s substantial for a person but still modest for a machine.\\n\\nWhat’s in `vault/raw` now:\\n- **69 files**\\n- about **11.7 MB** total\\n- mostly `.txt` research exports\\n- plus:\\n  - `MyActivity.html`\\n  - one `.pdf`\\n  - one `.xlsx`\\n- there are clear duplicates and near-duplicates\\n- there are clearly multiple project families, at least **Apollo** and **Aurelius**\\n\\nSo the next steps should be practical and staged.\\n\\n**Recommended pipeline, phase 2: robust project ingestion**\\n\\n1. **Invento\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L154-L204\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L154-L2