{"type":"message","id":"77a83abc","parentId":"d84abd4f","timestamp":"2026-04-16T08:26:07.345Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I found the rough edge. The project scaffolds are still placeholders, and the timelines are useful but too large and repetitive for clean retrieval.\n\nI’m going to turn those scaffolds into compact operational docs and create a dedicated LightRAG-ready pack with summaries plus canonical sources.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0156872873475ee30169e09d174c38819199098f0de172468d\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JsS1O7hFE8Wj3n7NKYQh8NYc|fc_0156872873475ee30169e09d189c8c8191ad94269d0ea7c69d","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/Clean/projects/apollo/master_context.md","content":"# Apollo Master Context\n\n## Project summary\nApollo is a local sovereign intelligence stack designed to consolidate dispersed research, prior architectural decisions, and project knowledge into a usable retrieval and orchestration system.\n\n## Core architecture\n- OpenClaw as the orchestrator and workspace agent\n- Ollama as the local inference layer\n- Docling for document purification and conversion\n- LightRAG as the knowledge graph and retrieval engine\n- Browserless and Crawl4AI as web acquisition tools\n- n8n and Postgres for automation and state tracking\n- Open WebUI as the human-facing interface\n\n## Current corpus state\n- Apollo has a small but high-value canonical source set\n- Gemini conversation history was recovered and partially transformed into a timeline\n- Exact and probable duplicates were identified before ingestion\n- Project folders and source buckets were created under `vault/Clean/projects/`\n\n## Current objective\nPrepare Apollo and Aurelius into a clean, canonical, retrieval-friendly corpus that LightRAG can ingest from `vault/Clean` without pulling in noisy duplicates or half-finished artifacts.\n\n## Constraints and design preferences\n- Prefer canonical sources over duplicate variants\n- Preserve provenance through file-based source references\n- Keep project boundaries explicit: Apollo, Aurelius, Shared, Other\n- Prefer smaller, cleaner operational docs over one giant merged memory file\n\n## Immediate next stage\n- Finalize operational docs for Apollo and Aurelius\n- Build a LightRAG-ready ingestion pack under `vault/Clean/ingest/`\n- Verify LightRAG indexing against the cleaned corpus, not the raw corpus\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/Clean/projects/apollo/master_context.md\",\"content\":\"# Apollo Master Context\\n\\n## Project summary\\nApollo is a local sovereign intelligence stack designed to consolidate dispersed research, prior architectural decisions, and project knowledge into a usable retrieval and orchestration system.\\n\\n## Core architecture\\n- OpenClaw as the orchestrator and workspace agent\\n- Ollama as the local inference layer\\n- Docling for document purification and conversion\\n- LightRAG as the knowledge graph and retrieval engine\\n- Browserless and Crawl4AI as web acquisition tools\\n- n8n and Postgres for automation and state tracking\\n- Open WebUI as the human-facing interface\\n\\n## Current corpus state\\n- Apollo has a small but high-value canonical source set\\n- Gemini conversation history was recovered and partially transformed into a timeline\\n- Exact and probable duplicates were identified before ingestion\\n- Project folders and source buckets were created under `vault/Clean/projects/`\\n\\n## Current objective\\nPrepare Apollo and Aurelius into a clean, canonical, retrieval-friendly corpus that LightRAG can ingest from `vault/Clean` without pulling in noisy duplicates or half-finished artifacts.\\n\\n## Constraints and design preferences\\n- Prefer canonical sources over duplicate variants\\n- Preserve provenance through file-based source references\\n- Keep project boundaries explicit: Apollo, Aurelius, Shared, Other\\n- Prefer smaller, cleaner operational docs over one giant merged memory file\\n\\n## Immediate next stage\\n- Finalize operational docs for Apollo and Aurelius\\n- Build a LightRAG-ready ingestion pack under `vault/Clean/ingest/`\\n- Verify LightRAG indexing against the cleaned corpus, not the raw corpus\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":466,"output":429,"cacheRead":38400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39295,"cost":{"input":0.001165,"output":0.006435,"cacheRead":0.0096,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0172}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776327958365,"responseId":"resp_0156872873475ee30169e09d167aac81918c83f6012e09f76a"}}
