{"type":"message","id":"dfa22faa","parentId":"ac55e801","timestamp":"2026-04-16T08:26:20.411Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_y34Ncfj74Ri2W00Po7oAbPKz|fc_0156872873475ee30169e09d2c09c88191947b5bb03d6fe320","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/Clean/projects/apollo/decisions.md","content":"# Apollo Decisions\n\n## Confirmed decisions\n- Use `vault/Clean` as the clean corpus layer for downstream ingestion\n- Deduplicate before ingestion rather than indexing raw exports blindly\n- Separate project knowledge into Apollo, Aurelius, Shared, and Other buckets\n- Treat Gemini export material as a source to be sliced and summarized, not ingested raw without cleanup\n- Use project-level docs such as `master_context.md`, `decisions.md`, `tasks.md`, and `deliverables.md` to improve retrieval quality\n- Align ingestion with the actual Docker stack, where LightRAG reads from `/app/data/inputs` mapped to `C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean`\n\n## Working assumptions\n- Case sensitivity is not an issue in the Windows-backed volume layout\n- The current compose stack is the active target architecture\n- Canonical Apollo sources should be preserved as evidence alongside summary docs\n\n## Open decisions\n- Whether to ingest full project timelines as-is, or keep only compact summaries plus canonical source docs\n- Whether to split large conversation-derived timelines into smaller thematic notes later\n- Whether to create a dedicated Apollo-only and Aurelius-only conversation extraction pass from Gemini history\n\n## Recommendation\nFor the next ingestion pass, include compact operational docs and canonical source files. Keep oversized raw timelines available for traceability, but do not make them the primary retrieval surface.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/Clean/projects/apollo/decisions.md\",\"content\":\"# Apollo Decisions\\n\\n## Confirmed decisions\\n- Use `vault/Clean` as the clean corpus layer for downstream ingestion\\n- Deduplicate before ingestion rather than indexing raw exports blindly\\n- Separate project knowledge into Apollo, Aurelius, Shared, and Other buckets\\n- Treat Gemini export material as a source to be sliced and summarized, not ingested raw without cleanup\\n- Use project-level docs such as `master_context.md`, `decisions.md`, `tasks.md`, and `deliverables.md` to improve retrieval quality\\n- Align ingestion with the actual Docker stack, where LightRAG reads from `/app/data/inputs` mapped to `C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean`\\n\\n## Working assumptions\\n- Case sensitivity is not an issue in the Windows-backed volume layout\\n- The current compose stack is the active target architecture\\n- Canonical Apollo sources should be preserved as evidence alongside summary docs\\n\\n## Open decisions\\n- Whether to ingest full project timelines as-is, or keep only compact summaries plus canonical source docs\\n- Whether to split large conversation-derived timelines into smaller thematic notes later\\n- Whether to create a dedicated Apollo-only and Aurelius-only conversation extraction pass from Gemini history\\n\\n## Recommendation\\nFor the next ingestion pass, include compact operational docs and canonical source files. Keep oversized raw timelines available for traceability, but do not make them the primary retrieval surface.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_McJfn2mwR6Lod5jrtyIxn0Se|fc_0156872873475ee30169e09d2c09d481918676fbf67603bf33","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/Clean/projects/apollo/tasks.md","content":"# Apollo Tasks\n\n## Now\n- Validate the cleaned project corpus layout under `vault/Clean`\n- Prepare a LightRAG-ready ingestion pack from canonical Apollo and Aurelius materials\n- Keep recovered conversation context available as provenance\n\n## Next\n- Test LightRAG ingestion behavior against the cleaned pack\n- Check whether summary docs improve retrieval quality relative to source-o