{"type":"message","id":"1cb52480","parentId":"707fe7b6","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:29:02.178Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Yes, conceptually.\n\nThe clean way in OpenClaw is not really “forking” this exact chat transcript in-place, but spawning a **new parallel session** for a branch of work:\n- either an isolated sub-agent run\n- or a persistent side session if you want that branch to continue over time\n\nThat works well for things like:\n- one branch for Apollo corpus analysis\n- another for Aurelius protocol extraction\n- another for LightRAG ingestion planning\n\nSo, yes, we can branch the work. If you want, I can spin up a separate analysis session for a specific subtask and keep this thread as the coordinator.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0156872873475ee30169e0e41c208481919903f1748f38a1dc\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":60793,"output":140,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60933,"cost":{"input":0.15198250000000002,"output":0.0021,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1540825}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776346135731,"responseId":"resp_0156872873475ee30169e0e4188e3481919efc05b7e229ddb0"}}
